1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,960
Rituals, beliefs, and myths in this series are a work of fiction and in no regard refer to religions or faiths of any certain cultures.

2
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:16,920
Fate is woven by three forces.

3
00:00:18,080 --> 00:00:22,240
However, the fate of some is made to be
more complicated than that.

4
00:00:22,600 --> 00:00:23,640
Li Puo was misguided.

5
00:00:23,880 --> 00:00:25,760
He thought Qi Rong would
cherish and have mercy on him.

6
00:00:27,280 --> 00:00:30,520
But in reality, any higher power

7
00:00:30,680 --> 00:00:33,320
is incapable of playing favorites
with any human being.

8
00:00:33,680 --> 00:00:35,120
Be that heaven or demons,

9
00:00:35,120 --> 00:00:36,200
they’re no different.

10
00:00:38,120 --> 00:00:38,680
Yes.

11
00:00:39,160 --> 00:00:39,880
They’re no different.

12
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:53,120
Heaven or demons, they’re no different.

13
00:02:55,840 --> 00:02:59,040
I bow my humble head to
the great and powerful Lord Warrior.

14
00:03:37,320 --> 00:03:38,960
I was foolish before,

15
00:03:40,440 --> 00:03:42,240
blindsided by what I thought I knew.

16
00:03:44,600 --> 00:03:48,760
It was arrogant to think such a great power
was a demon to be defeated.

17
00:03:50,720 --> 00:03:52,320
The truth is otherwise.

18
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:56,240
You are called a demon

19
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:58,720
simply because you refused to bow down.

20
00:04:01,600 --> 00:04:03,400
How can the world survive
without a force like yours?

21
00:04:09,280 --> 00:04:11,360
Outrage isn’t evil.

22
00:04:12,560 --> 00:04:16,040
As long as tyrants exist,

23
00:04:17,560 --> 00:04:19,000
you must continue to exist.

24
00:04:24,800 --> 00:04:26,080
A power as great as yours

25
00:04:27,200 --> 00:04:29,320
should be exercised against injustice,

26
00:04:31,440 --> 00:04:37,000
not to cause commotion
that feeds man’s twisted ego.

27
00:04:43,240 --> 00:04:45,400
The great and powerful Lord Warrior,

28
00:04:48,360 --> 00:04:50,680
please return to your peaceful slumber.

29
00:04:52,080 --> 00:04:56,400
When a tyrant pillages his own people,

30
00:04:57,640 --> 00:05:05,440
that is when someone virtuous
shall awaken you to protect the world.

31
00:05:06,920 --> 00:05:10,160
Is that not the way it is supposed to be?

32
00:05:23,400 --> 00:05:25,040
Is he really gonna listen to Niran?

33
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:27,600
Of course.

34
00:05:28,320 --> 00:05:29,680
Not to his voice,

35
00:05:30,640 --> 00:05:32,040
but to his intention within.

36
00:06:52,880 --> 00:06:54,360
What are you gonna do with it?

37
00:06:56,159 --> 00:06:57,480
Probably find a place for it.

38
00:06:58,560 --> 00:06:59,400
I see.

39
00:07:00,240 --> 00:07:00,840
Here.

40
00:07:03,080 --> 00:07:05,760
Well, to celebrate a job well done.

41
00:07:08,520 --> 00:07:09,040
Sure.

42
00:07:09,240 --> 00:07:09,680
Cheers.

43
00:07:10,360 --> 00:07:11,000
Cheers.

44
00:07:11,280 --> 00:07:12,400
We are The Wu!

45
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:14,720
Yeah.

46
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:16,560
We are The Wu.

47
00:07:17,480 --> 00:07:18,160
Hey!

48
00:07:18,560 --> 00:07:20,360
You finally stopped being a tsundere.

49
00:07:20,800 --> 00:07:21,880
Now that’s more like it, man.

50
00:07:22,480 --> 00:07:23,240
Shout it out.

51
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:24,520
We are The Wu!

52
00:07:24,880 --> 00:07:26,360
Yeah!

53
00:07:27,520 --> 00:07:29,400
You’re a freaking dork.

54
00:07:29,400 --> 00:07:30,600
We really are The Wu!

55
00:07:32,360 --> 00:07:32,800
Here.

56
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:33,400
Thanks.

57
00:07:34,640 --> 00:07:35,400
For you.

58
00:07:38,760 --> 00:07:39,520
So…

59
00:07:39,800 --> 00:07:42,200
What’s next for you guys?

60
00:07:43,680 --> 00:07:44,320
Me?

61
00:07:44,840 --> 00:07:46,760
I’ll probably stick with the drum.

62
00:07:46,960 --> 00:07:49,320
Keep me in the loop if you
have a fun job like this again.

63
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:50,120
I’m short on money.

64
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:51,440
Badly.

65
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:54,880
I’m not sure what’s next for me.

66
00:07:55,320 --> 00:07:56,120
But…

67
00:07:57,640 --> 00:07:59,440
I want to try writing a book.

68
00:08:00,360 --> 00:08:02,760
Maybe I can write something
about this experience.

69
00:08:04,320 --> 00:08:08,560
Honestly, going through something
like this makes me think.

70
00:08:08,680 --> 00:08:13,160
We really had been reckless,
not afraid of a single crap.

71
00:08:14,280 --> 00:08:16,440
But when we were at death’s door,

72
00:08:16,640 --> 00:08:19,520
I can’t help but think that life might
actually be worth something.

73
00:08:20,040 --> 00:08:21,120
I agree.

74
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:22,880
Same here, bud!

75
00:08:24,920 --> 00:08:26,480
You know what you need to do?

76
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:28,640
I’m going back to college.

77
00:08:28,880 --> 00:08:31,640
So you guys should too.

78
00:08:32,480 --> 00:08:33,760
What? Why?

79
00:08:34,280 --> 00:08:36,320
Just come along with me.

80
00:08:36,480 --> 00:08:37,880
I’ll make sure you all have a degree.

81
00:08:42,320 --> 00:08:43,080
And you, Fei?

82
00:08:43,799 --> 00:08:44,600
What’s next for you?

83
00:08:47,640 --> 00:08:48,920
What’s next for me?

84
00:08:51,560 --> 00:08:52,680
That’s none of your business.

85
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:53,760
Stay out of it.

86
00:08:54,240 --> 00:08:54,920
Oi!

87
00:08:55,280 --> 00:08:56,440
I’m just trying to be nice.

88
00:08:57,800 --> 00:08:58,880
What’s next for you?

89
00:08:59,400 --> 00:09:01,280
Wait, no— I don’t want to know.

90
00:09:01,480 --> 00:09:01,840
You…

91
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:04,680
She got him good.

92
00:09:07,440 --> 00:09:08,320
Speaking of which,

93
00:09:08,720 --> 00:09:09,840
that thing almost killed you.

94
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:11,160
You sure you wanna keep drinking?

95
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:13,600
Why should I stop?

96
00:09:14,320 --> 00:09:16,560
Heaven never forbids
such a simple pleasure.

97
00:09:32,200 --> 00:09:33,120
But honestly,

98
00:09:34,920 --> 00:09:35,920
all this time,

99
00:09:38,680 --> 00:09:39,680
I didn’t consume no liquor.

100
00:09:45,960 --> 00:09:47,480
I let it consume me.

101
00:09:59,680 --> 00:10:03,440
So is it… really over now?

102
00:10:05,360 --> 00:10:06,720
I think the protesters are going home.

103
00:10:06,960 --> 00:10:08,320
The government just came out to say

104
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:11,760
they’ll deal with protestors
with real weapons.

105
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:16,840
MOB CRACKDOWN

106
00:10:16,840 --> 00:10:18,200
AT 6.00 P.M. TODAY

107
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:19,560
WITH REAL BULLETS

108
00:10:19,560 --> 00:10:20,560
FALL BACK. #MOBCRACKDOWN

109
00:10:20,560 --> 00:10:21,360
GO HOME. #MOBCRACKDOWN

110
00:10:21,360 --> 00:10:21,880
STAY SAFE. #MOBCRACKDOWN

111
00:10:21,880 --> 00:10:22,280
GO HOME! #MOBCRACKDOWN

112
00:10:22,280 --> 00:10:22,760
REAL BULLETS. #MOBCRACKDOWN

113
00:10:24,400 --> 00:10:26,320
Good thing we sealed Qi Rong.

114
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:29,720
Otherwise, it would have kept people
enraged and refused to go home.

115
00:10:30,360 --> 00:10:32,400
But there are still people who won’t leave.

116
00:10:33,120 --> 00:10:34,240
Hundreds of people.

117
00:10:34,480 --> 00:10:35,400
FALL BACK = DIE
I’D RATHER STAY. #MOBCRACKDOWN

118
00:10:35,400 --> 00:10:36,200
I can’t go home.

119
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:37,520
PROTESTERS REFUSE TO GO HOME
I’d starve to death anyway if I went home.

120
00:10:37,520 --> 00:10:38,760
PROTESTERS REFUSE TO GO HOME
Then I’ll stay and die here.

121
00:10:38,840 --> 00:10:39,840
GO HOME IF YOU WANT. I’LL STAY!
#MOBCRACKDOWN

122
00:10:39,840 --> 00:10:40,720
FIGHT TO THE DEATH.
#MOBCRACKDOWN

123
00:10:40,720 --> 00:10:41,560
I’LL DIE FIGHTING./NOTHING TO LOSE./STAY STRONG.

124
00:10:43,720 --> 00:10:45,480
What will become of these people?

125
00:10:54,720 --> 00:10:55,200
Fei.

126
00:10:57,120 --> 00:10:59,000
You need to take me to
the Prime Minister right now.

127
00:11:09,600 --> 00:11:12,080
Hello, my beloved people.

128
00:11:12,920 --> 00:11:15,240
I have an important
announcement to make,

129
00:11:15,720 --> 00:11:21,280
regarding the current political turmoil
that has been difficult for the country

130
00:11:22,160 --> 00:11:24,640
economically, as well as
in terms of security.

131
00:11:25,760 --> 00:11:32,200
The MPs and I are more than
willing to hear your voice,

132
00:11:33,080 --> 00:11:39,040
however, we simply cannot ignore
disruptions and public defacement,

133
00:11:39,840 --> 00:11:44,960
as well as any other actions
that violate other people’s rights.

134
00:11:46,120 --> 00:11:51,360
Therefore, we must take an extreme
measure to secure back the perimeter

135
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:53,720
at 6.00 p.m. today.

136
00:11:54,640 --> 00:11:59,440
This message goes out to all the people
at the protest who wish the country well…

137
00:12:00,080 --> 00:12:01,640
Please go home.

138
00:12:02,400 --> 00:12:07,040
Those who refuse to leave the perimeter
will be treated as terrorists.

139
00:12:08,120 --> 00:12:15,600
(I stand by my word that
we value all of your opinions...)

140
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:17,120
You sure you won’t change your mind?

141
00:12:36,280 --> 00:12:37,240
He’s ready to see you.

142
00:12:37,880 --> 00:12:38,920
You only have 10 minutes.

143
00:12:56,400 --> 00:12:57,040
Hello, sir.

144
00:12:57,520 --> 00:12:58,240
Hello, Fei.

145
00:13:03,400 --> 00:13:04,560
Hello, Mr. Prime Minister.

146
00:13:05,120 --> 00:13:06,120
Hello, Master Niran.

147
00:13:07,720 --> 00:13:09,680
Fei talks about you a lot.

148
00:13:13,600 --> 00:13:14,120
Please have a seat.

149
00:13:18,320 --> 00:13:21,720
I must thank all of you.

150
00:13:23,480 --> 00:13:24,480
You saved me.

151
00:13:27,800 --> 00:13:28,360
No…

152
00:13:30,760 --> 00:13:32,120
You saved the country.

153
00:13:32,920 --> 00:13:36,440
I don’t think I can accept your gratitude, sir.

154
00:13:39,200 --> 00:13:41,440
Because even though the demon
has been defeated,

155
00:13:42,600 --> 00:13:45,640
the real disaster for this country
is still present.

156
00:13:46,840 --> 00:13:48,160
It might even just begin.

157
00:13:52,880 --> 00:13:53,640
Leave us alone.

158
00:14:03,280 --> 00:14:04,080
Please go on.

159
00:14:06,440 --> 00:14:09,120
There is something far more dangerous

160
00:14:10,160 --> 00:14:12,840
and even more of a threat to
a country than a demon.

161
00:14:17,680 --> 00:14:22,040
That is the fact that a leader
lacks the mandate of heaven.

162
00:14:22,040 --> 00:14:22,720
Niran.

163
00:14:22,840 --> 00:14:23,520
What are you saying?

164
00:14:23,520 --> 00:14:25,560
A demon is an external threat.

165
00:14:25,800 --> 00:14:26,840
Once defeated,

166
00:14:27,880 --> 00:14:29,600
everything will be back to normal.

167
00:14:30,560 --> 00:14:33,840
But when a leader lacks
the mandate of heaven,

168
00:14:35,040 --> 00:14:36,720
the country will be destroyed from within.

169
00:14:36,720 --> 00:14:37,520
Niran, stop it!

170
00:14:37,520 --> 00:14:38,160
Fei.

171
00:14:45,360 --> 00:14:48,120
Every system will gradually decline.

172
00:14:49,880 --> 00:14:53,680
People will fight among themselves,
an endless skirmish,

173
00:14:55,080 --> 00:14:56,600
becoming a chronic issue,

174
00:14:57,720 --> 00:15:01,160
and the nation will eventually fall.

175
00:15:03,480 --> 00:15:05,200
To prevent that from happening,

176
00:15:06,360 --> 00:15:08,760
will you allow me to perform a ritual to see

177
00:15:10,240 --> 00:15:14,120
whether the mandate of heaven
is still with you?

178
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:19,040
Do we have time?

179
00:15:20,360 --> 00:15:22,240
It won’t take long, sir.

180
00:15:27,200 --> 00:15:27,560
Mirror.

181
00:15:30,960 --> 00:15:31,360
Huh?

182
00:15:34,160 --> 00:15:34,640
Mirror.

183
00:15:36,080 --> 00:15:36,480
Oh.

184
00:15:42,560 --> 00:15:45,400
If you’re gonna stick around,
be professional!

185
00:15:45,960 --> 00:15:46,280
Jerk.

186
00:15:52,920 --> 00:15:53,760
Please.

187
00:15:54,680 --> 00:15:56,240
This is for your own good.

188
00:15:57,320 --> 00:15:59,920
We’ll see if you’re still fit
to run this country.

189
00:16:45,440 --> 00:16:47,440
If the mandate of heaven is still with you,

190
00:16:48,600 --> 00:16:50,200
it will show in the reflection.

191
00:16:53,280 --> 00:16:54,520
If the opposite is true,

192
00:16:55,720 --> 00:16:56,720
you will see something else.

193
00:17:08,680 --> 00:17:13,480
May heaven lend its power
to verify this man’s mandate.

194
00:17:21,119 --> 00:17:22,440
You are a former soldier,

195
00:17:23,359 --> 00:17:26,760
who quit your military service
to become a politician.

196
00:17:28,079 --> 00:17:29,640
You did not wish for power,

197
00:17:30,320 --> 00:17:32,840
only to make a change for this country.

198
00:17:34,480 --> 00:17:36,320
You wanted people to be one

199
00:17:37,040 --> 00:17:38,640
at a time when everyone was at odds.

200
00:17:41,080 --> 00:17:45,200
You wanted to make this country
a happy home for all.

201
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:48,400
You became the beacon of hope.

202
00:17:49,680 --> 00:17:51,840
Despite the various hurdles in your way,

203
00:17:52,760 --> 00:17:53,960
you never gave in.

204
00:17:55,040 --> 00:17:57,040
You fought alongside your people.

205
00:17:57,760 --> 00:18:04,760
Is someone who was trusted by his people
worthy of the mandate?

206
00:18:08,400 --> 00:18:10,560
The answer is in the reflection
on that mirror.

207
00:18:17,120 --> 00:18:18,800
After going through many obstacles,

208
00:18:19,600 --> 00:18:24,080
you felt it was time you came into power,

209
00:18:25,680 --> 00:18:28,000
otherwise, you would not be able
to make a change.

210
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:34,240
That was the reason
you accepted some dirty money,

211
00:18:35,440 --> 00:18:40,400
because you knew money played
an important role in an election.

212
00:18:41,680 --> 00:18:43,160
You swallowed your own pride again

213
00:18:44,400 --> 00:18:48,480
when you agreed to form a coalition
with politicians who were enemies.

214
00:18:50,120 --> 00:18:52,280
You shared some benefits with them,

215
00:18:53,160 --> 00:18:57,280
hoping that you would secure
this position of power

216
00:18:58,400 --> 00:19:00,400
and be able to do something
for the country.

217
00:19:05,240 --> 00:19:07,960
Isn’t that a vision
of a respectable leader?

218
00:19:10,880 --> 00:19:15,320
Someone who disregards his principles
for the greater good

219
00:19:16,600 --> 00:19:21,960
and someone obsessed with righteousness but never acts selfless.

220
00:19:23,640 --> 00:19:27,560
Which man deserves to have
the mandate of heaven?

221
00:19:35,320 --> 00:19:38,440
You received the mandate of the people
to run this country,

222
00:19:40,120 --> 00:19:42,920
but you also need the mandate of heaven.

223
00:19:57,520 --> 00:19:58,560
But in reality,

224
00:20:01,720 --> 00:20:03,000
you know better than anybody

225
00:20:04,080 --> 00:20:06,680
what you’ve been doing

226
00:20:08,040 --> 00:20:09,360
in the past two years of your term,

227
00:20:11,840 --> 00:20:14,760
between making a change
like you initially wanted to

228
00:20:15,800 --> 00:20:18,160
and managing the benefits
of your allies and enemies

229
00:20:19,160 --> 00:20:21,480
to keep yourself in position.

230
00:20:26,600 --> 00:20:28,000
You don’t need to answer me.

231
00:20:29,200 --> 00:20:31,000
You know the answer well enough.

232
00:20:33,120 --> 00:20:35,200
A leader who is elected by the people

233
00:20:36,440 --> 00:20:39,040
is naturally susceptible to be expelled
by the same people.

234
00:20:40,760 --> 00:20:42,960
The people might have been
under the demon’s influence,

235
00:20:44,640 --> 00:20:48,480
but can you really deny that,
among those people,

236
00:20:49,560 --> 00:20:51,920
no one was affected by your actions?

237
00:20:54,080 --> 00:20:58,000
You are in power because of your people.

238
00:20:58,960 --> 00:21:00,760
But you are using that very same power…

239
00:21:02,160 --> 00:21:03,920
as death sentences for your own people.

240
00:21:05,360 --> 00:21:10,240
Do you think the mandate of heaven
still favors such a leader, sir?

241
00:21:41,360 --> 00:21:42,440
Heaven is supreme,

242
00:21:43,600 --> 00:21:45,880
but it also resides within our own mind.

243
00:21:47,560 --> 00:21:49,600
You simply need to ask yourself truthfully.

244
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:52,000
The answer

245
00:21:53,120 --> 00:21:54,520
will be as good as if
it was given by heaven.

246
00:22:39,600 --> 00:22:44,240
If the answer was
what you feel it should be,

247
00:22:45,680 --> 00:22:47,040
do you expect me to give up

248
00:22:49,200 --> 00:22:51,880
and let the 10 years I’ve been fighting
go to waste

249
00:22:53,680 --> 00:22:56,120
without ever bringing anything to fruition?

250
00:23:01,280 --> 00:23:02,840
If heaven still favors you,

251
00:23:03,520 --> 00:23:05,000
and the people still choose you,

252
00:23:06,360 --> 00:23:08,120
you can always start again.

253
00:23:13,280 --> 00:23:16,840
If my answer was the opposite?

254
00:23:18,360 --> 00:23:19,360
If that is the case,

255
00:23:20,240 --> 00:23:22,720
we must perform an
appeal to heaven ritual.

256
00:23:33,280 --> 00:23:34,560
What do you think you’re doing, Niran?

257
00:23:35,120 --> 00:23:37,520
I thought you just wanted to convince him
to change his mind about tonight.

258
00:23:37,760 --> 00:23:39,360
But you’ve been talking nonsense,

259
00:23:39,360 --> 00:23:40,760
and what the hell was that fake ritual?

260
00:23:42,280 --> 00:23:45,480
You know everything that happened
in that room was true.

261
00:23:46,080 --> 00:23:47,000
How could you not see it?

262
00:23:48,320 --> 00:23:49,560
Maybe he’s under a lot of pressure.

263
00:23:50,400 --> 00:23:51,920
It’s not easy being a leader.

264
00:23:51,920 --> 00:23:53,080
But there’s a line,

265
00:23:53,800 --> 00:23:55,240
not just one that we shouldn’t cross,

266
00:23:56,360 --> 00:23:58,040
but mustn’t cross.

267
00:23:59,680 --> 00:24:02,560
You know he’s the beacon of hope.

268
00:24:03,320 --> 00:24:04,640
He’s my only hope.

269
00:24:05,240 --> 00:24:06,560
He’s the beacon of hope for this country.

270
00:24:06,560 --> 00:24:07,640
Who exactly are you talking about?

271
00:24:09,840 --> 00:24:11,760
The patriotic politician from 15 years ago,

272
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:16,200
or the Prime Minister who is about
to kill his own people?

273
00:24:19,280 --> 00:24:20,080
I’ll wait until 2 p.m.

274
00:24:21,240 --> 00:24:22,800
If he refuses to resign,

275
00:24:26,360 --> 00:24:28,280
I’ll perform the appeal to heaven ritual.

276
00:24:29,600 --> 00:24:31,000
Everything needs to end

277
00:24:31,800 --> 00:24:33,080
before there’s an irreversible loss.

278
00:24:35,120 --> 00:24:38,320
You do realize that it isn’t a ritual
to perform lightly?

279
00:24:39,520 --> 00:24:40,960
If heaven turns you down,

280
00:24:42,480 --> 00:24:45,080
who knows how long it will be before
you can connect with nature again?

281
00:24:46,800 --> 00:24:48,560
Are you going to risk
your being Wu for this?

282
00:24:57,200 --> 00:24:58,840
What’s the point of being Wu, then?

283
00:25:01,040 --> 00:25:02,600
To keep our power to ourselves

284
00:25:04,200 --> 00:25:05,800
and not doing the right thing?

285
00:25:11,760 --> 00:25:13,320
Do you still fancy yourself Wu?

286
00:25:29,280 --> 00:25:30,440
If I am no Wu,

287
00:25:31,720 --> 00:25:32,640
what am I?

288
00:25:57,360 --> 00:25:58,440
Oh, Fei.

289
00:26:03,240 --> 00:26:06,480
I apologize for—

290
00:26:09,840 --> 00:26:10,520
Forget it.

291
00:26:18,120 --> 00:26:19,840
We’ve known each other
more than 10 years now.

292
00:26:22,280 --> 00:26:24,160
You’ve been an amazing advisor.

293
00:26:29,800 --> 00:26:30,720
You saved me.

294
00:26:37,280 --> 00:26:38,160
It is unfortunate

295
00:26:40,840 --> 00:26:42,240
that this is as far as I can go.

296
00:26:44,000 --> 00:26:45,560
I gave my blood, sweat, and tears

297
00:26:47,200 --> 00:26:48,360
to seize this power.

298
00:26:51,440 --> 00:26:53,240
But I have so little time…

299
00:26:54,840 --> 00:26:59,320
So little time I didn’t get anything done.

300
00:27:03,960 --> 00:27:06,080
Heaven allowed me hopes,

301
00:27:09,160 --> 00:27:10,960
but not enough time
to make those hopes realized.

302
00:27:13,840 --> 00:27:15,120
You always have time, sir.

303
00:27:19,120 --> 00:27:19,560
No.

304
00:27:21,240 --> 00:27:22,720
I know my situation well enough.

305
00:27:33,880 --> 00:27:38,000
What your associate said he would do…

306
00:27:40,040 --> 00:27:41,400
Should I be concerned?

307
00:27:48,000 --> 00:27:49,720
Oh, you idiot!

308
00:27:50,520 --> 00:27:51,880
I’ll say I agree with Fei.

309
00:27:52,080 --> 00:27:54,200
I thought you were just going to
convince him to change his mind,

310
00:27:54,280 --> 00:27:56,840
but you just had to threaten him, huh?

311
00:27:57,000 --> 00:27:58,560
Are you out of your goddamn mind?

312
00:27:58,920 --> 00:28:00,960
You think a guy like me could
change a Prime Minister’s mind?

313
00:28:01,360 --> 00:28:02,640
It was obvious he was deadset on it.

314
00:28:02,760 --> 00:28:04,760
I swear he’s not letting you off the hook.

315
00:28:04,760 --> 00:28:06,040
Nothing happens yet, you know?

316
00:28:06,360 --> 00:28:07,600
There’s no need to worry about it.

317
00:28:07,680 --> 00:28:09,080
I’ll be damned if I don’t!

318
00:28:09,280 --> 00:28:10,760
I don’t think we can even go home today.

319
00:28:10,760 --> 00:28:12,960
Shit! It’s definitely dangerous for us now.

320
00:28:14,560 --> 00:28:15,640
I’m gonna go take a piss.

321
00:28:15,760 --> 00:28:18,000
You come up with a place
where we can lay low for now.

322
00:28:18,560 --> 00:28:19,640
Damn it.

323
00:28:25,880 --> 00:28:26,280
Hello.

324
00:28:26,640 --> 00:28:28,680
Niran, you need to hide right now.

325
00:28:28,960 --> 00:28:29,320
What?

326
00:28:29,480 --> 00:28:30,160
What was that?

327
00:28:30,280 --> 00:28:31,800
(You need to hide right away!)

328
00:28:33,800 --> 00:28:34,280
Pete!

329
00:28:34,600 --> 00:28:35,120
Pete!

330
00:28:35,720 --> 00:28:36,200
Pete!

331
00:28:37,920 --> 00:28:38,920
What the hell!

332
00:28:40,280 --> 00:28:41,160
Let go of me!

333
00:28:43,160 --> 00:28:43,600
Shit!

334
00:28:43,600 --> 00:28:44,360
Niran!

335
00:28:47,000 --> 00:28:47,640
Shit!

336
00:28:50,080 --> 00:28:50,880
Excuse me.

337
00:28:51,240 --> 00:28:52,120
I’m gonna borrow your bike.

338
00:28:52,120 --> 00:28:52,840
My friend’s being kidnapped.

339
00:28:52,960 --> 00:28:53,680
Alright?

340
00:28:53,680 --> 00:28:54,480
Please.

341
00:28:54,480 --> 00:28:55,360
Will you let me borrow it?

342
00:29:33,680 --> 00:29:34,440
Pete?

343
00:30:02,800 --> 00:30:04,120
Let my friend go, you bastards!

344
00:30:50,880 --> 00:30:51,440
Hey!

345
00:30:52,240 --> 00:30:53,040
Let my friend go

346
00:30:55,400 --> 00:30:56,240
or I pull the trigger.

347
00:30:59,800 --> 00:31:00,400
Pete.

348
00:31:00,680 --> 00:31:01,200
Get in the car.

349
00:31:09,560 --> 00:31:10,240
Go!

350
00:31:17,560 --> 00:31:18,560
Why’d you take their car?

351
00:31:18,560 --> 00:31:19,600
We should have taken the motorbike.

352
00:31:19,600 --> 00:31:21,320
This car is safer than your damn bike.

353
00:31:21,320 --> 00:31:22,200
Safe, my ass!

354
00:31:22,200 --> 00:31:22,960
It’s their car.

355
00:31:22,960 --> 00:31:24,320
They can probably track us.

356
00:31:35,200 --> 00:31:36,160
Get the hell out.

357
00:31:36,400 --> 00:31:36,920
What?

358
00:31:37,280 --> 00:31:37,640
Why?

359
00:31:37,640 --> 00:31:39,840
Just get out of the car
before they all get here.

360
00:31:39,960 --> 00:31:42,080
I’m going to lure them away from you.

361
00:31:42,280 --> 00:31:44,560
Take this time to perform whatever
ritual you’re going to perform.

362
00:31:44,760 --> 00:31:45,680
Go on and get it done already.

363
00:31:45,680 --> 00:31:46,640
You jerk, are you insane?
How can I leave you—

364
00:31:46,640 --> 00:31:47,320
Hey!

365
00:31:48,880 --> 00:31:49,840
Trust me a little.

366
00:31:51,160 --> 00:31:52,600
We’re partners.

367
00:31:53,600 --> 00:31:55,560
You expect this trust
to be one-sided or what?

368
00:32:06,400 --> 00:32:06,880
Okay.

369
00:32:19,360 --> 00:32:20,480
Don’t you freaking die, you jerk.

370
00:32:25,120 --> 00:32:26,000
I ain’t gonna.

371
00:32:26,600 --> 00:32:29,560
You may have heaven on your side,

372
00:32:29,800 --> 00:32:32,840
but I have a demon, you know?

373
00:32:33,440 --> 00:32:34,560
I’m just as cool as you.

374
00:32:40,080 --> 00:32:41,440
You do what you can.

375
00:32:42,440 --> 00:32:44,040
And I’ll do what I can.

376
00:33:42,280 --> 00:33:43,000
Keep your gun.

377
00:33:43,480 --> 00:33:44,560
There’s just two of them.

378
00:33:44,560 --> 00:33:45,640
Let’s not make a big deal out of this.

379
00:33:53,960 --> 00:33:54,680
Come out.

380
00:33:55,080 --> 00:33:56,080
Come on out.

381
00:33:58,640 --> 00:33:59,520
Come on.

382
00:33:59,520 --> 00:34:00,520
Come out.

383
00:34:01,160 --> 00:34:02,120
Come out.

384
00:34:02,200 --> 00:34:03,120
Come out.

385
00:34:03,520 --> 00:34:04,400
Come on out!

386
00:36:51,440 --> 00:36:52,080
Pete.

387
00:36:53,400 --> 00:36:55,280
You shouldn’t think of it as a curse.

388
00:36:57,120 --> 00:36:59,080
However it was put inside you,

389
00:37:00,080 --> 00:37:02,080
it was given to you by your parents.

390
00:37:02,960 --> 00:37:04,600
You should think of it as a blessing,

391
00:37:04,880 --> 00:37:05,680
not a curse.

392
00:37:40,960 --> 00:37:44,520
Right now, the leader lacks
the mandate of heaven.

393
00:37:45,720 --> 00:37:47,160
Despite his incompetence,

394
00:37:47,920 --> 00:37:51,240
he insists on staying in power.

395
00:37:55,640 --> 00:37:56,960
The mandate of heaven
must not be violated.

396
00:37:57,920 --> 00:38:00,920
May heaven take action on this matter.

397
00:38:01,800 --> 00:38:04,360
May heaven accept this appeal.

398
00:38:12,640 --> 00:38:13,920
(You are no Wu.)

399
00:38:15,240 --> 00:38:16,520
(Do you still fancy yourself Wu?)

400
00:38:18,040 --> 00:38:18,800
(If you are not Wu…)

401
00:38:18,800 --> 00:38:21,120
(...how long will it be before
you can connect with nature again?)

402
00:38:21,360 --> 00:38:23,400
(Any more questions?)

403
00:39:44,280 --> 00:39:47,320
Everyone in our party has agreed

404
00:39:48,240 --> 00:39:52,520
that your decision will bring about
a long-term defeat for us.

405
00:39:53,760 --> 00:39:54,760
If you don’t resign,

406
00:39:55,800 --> 00:39:57,960
in the next motion of censure,

407
00:39:59,320 --> 00:40:02,280
all of us will not vote for you.

408
00:40:03,640 --> 00:40:09,560
Lt.Gen, Chaisak Kraiadirek,
the Prime Minister, has just resigned.

409
00:40:10,400 --> 00:40:13,160
To keep with the political principles,

410
00:40:14,520 --> 00:40:17,760
I resign from my position
as the Prime Minister.

411
00:40:18,600 --> 00:40:19,680
(Our policies…)

412
00:40:20,320 --> 00:40:21,240
Stay still.

413
00:40:21,280 --> 00:40:21,960
We’re almost done.

414
00:40:22,400 --> 00:40:24,080
(...under the caretaker regime.)

415
00:40:24,520 --> 00:40:25,040
You jerk!

416
00:40:25,040 --> 00:40:25,760
That hurts!

417
00:40:28,200 --> 00:40:31,720
I let it out for a few minutes
and it took such a toll on my body?

418
00:40:32,200 --> 00:40:34,000
Blame your stupidity for letting it out, dude.

419
00:40:34,240 --> 00:40:35,920
Man, there were ten of them.

420
00:40:36,120 --> 00:40:38,680
If I didn’t borrow its power,
I might actually be dead—

421
00:40:39,560 --> 00:40:40,800
I said it hurts!

422
00:40:43,560 --> 00:40:44,080
That’s good.

423
00:40:45,400 --> 00:40:48,720
At least you kept your promise
and stayed alive.

424
00:40:53,640 --> 00:40:54,920
You forgot something.

425
00:40:56,920 --> 00:40:57,400
What is it?

426
00:40:58,960 --> 00:41:01,040
You forgot to praise me, you idiot!

427
00:41:01,360 --> 00:41:05,200
I let it out, but I was in total control.

428
00:41:05,200 --> 00:41:05,880
How’s that?

429
00:41:06,600 --> 00:41:07,480
Am I amazing?

430
00:41:10,760 --> 00:41:11,080
Yeah.

431
00:41:11,880 --> 00:41:12,160
Sure.

432
00:41:12,800 --> 00:41:13,720
You’re a damn champion.

433
00:41:14,280 --> 00:41:14,960
No one’s more amazing than you.

434
00:41:15,440 --> 00:41:16,160
Damn.

435
00:41:16,520 --> 00:41:17,840
It was one to ten, man.

436
00:41:19,760 --> 00:41:21,000
I’m freaking amazing.

437
00:41:21,000 --> 00:41:22,160
I’m not just amazing.

438
00:41:22,240 --> 00:41:22,560
Yeah.

439
00:41:22,560 --> 00:41:23,320
I’m freaking amazing.

440
00:41:23,320 --> 00:41:23,720
Yeah.

441
00:41:24,120 --> 00:41:24,960
Freaking amazing.

442
00:41:24,960 --> 00:41:26,000
Hurts like hell, though.

443
00:41:39,440 --> 00:41:39,760
Pete.

444
00:41:41,120 --> 00:41:41,360
Yeah?

445
00:41:45,160 --> 00:41:46,360
Thank you.

446
00:41:50,760 --> 00:41:52,280
Thank you for staying by my side.

447
00:41:58,520 --> 00:41:59,960
I should thank you.

448
00:42:06,000 --> 00:42:07,640
Think back to the first day you met me.

449
00:42:11,160 --> 00:42:13,720
Thank you for coming into my life.

450
00:42:17,520 --> 00:42:20,240
You pulled me up from a dark place.

451
00:42:25,080 --> 00:42:25,440
Nah.

452
00:42:27,560 --> 00:42:29,640
You slapped me into shape as well.

453
00:42:35,400 --> 00:42:35,960
Well…

454
00:42:38,120 --> 00:42:39,440
Do you still think it’s a mistake,

455
00:42:41,640 --> 00:42:43,120
binding your soul with mine?

456
00:42:52,400 --> 00:42:52,840
No.

457
00:42:57,080 --> 00:42:57,760
I think…

458
00:42:58,600 --> 00:43:03,280
This might be the rightest thing
I’ve ever done in my entire life.

459
00:43:11,920 --> 00:43:12,520
Smiling.

460
00:43:12,880 --> 00:43:14,000
That got you smiling, huh?

461
00:43:14,560 --> 00:43:15,320
You proud of that?

462
00:43:19,960 --> 00:43:21,000
Well, Mr. Champion.

463
00:43:22,160 --> 00:43:22,960
Let’s get back to dressing your wounds.

464
00:43:22,960 --> 00:43:24,280
No, no, no.

465
00:43:24,480 --> 00:43:25,200
That’s enough.

466
00:43:25,520 --> 00:43:26,200
It hurts.

467
00:43:26,640 --> 00:43:30,360
Don’t think you can do whatever you want
just because you have that monkey in you.

468
00:43:30,520 --> 00:43:31,680
Your wounds don’t heal on their own.

469
00:43:34,600 --> 00:43:35,120
Gotcha!

470
00:43:36,400 --> 00:43:36,640
You idiot…

471
00:43:38,040 --> 00:43:38,520
Die.

472
00:43:39,520 --> 00:43:42,600
As Wu, I have a new power.

473
00:43:43,280 --> 00:43:44,000
What power?

474
00:43:44,000 --> 00:43:45,560
To deal with you, obviously.

475
00:43:46,200 --> 00:43:48,560
Monkey Defeating Ethanol Spell!

476
00:43:49,240 --> 00:43:49,920
You jerk!

477
00:43:50,480 --> 00:43:52,160
You idiot, that hurts!

478
00:43:53,200 --> 00:43:54,840
That’s not fair.

479
00:44:05,640 --> 00:44:06,680
No! I’m still injured!

480
00:44:06,680 --> 00:44:08,240
That’s the only thing stopping me.

481
00:44:13,080 --> 00:44:14,960
(Life is determined by three forces.)

482
00:44:15,240 --> 00:44:15,640
(Heaven.)

483
00:44:16,400 --> 00:44:16,800
(Earth.)

484
00:44:18,040 --> 00:44:18,480
(Humanity.)

485
00:44:25,880 --> 00:44:28,280
(One question remains unanswered…)

486
00:44:29,960 --> 00:44:32,360
I’M TAKING A TEMPORARY NO-CONTACT BREAK UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE. THANK YOU FOR YOUR SUPPORT.
(Does a person live according to their own will,)

487
00:44:35,320 --> 00:44:36,680
(or is their life predestined?)

488
00:44:43,400 --> 00:44:44,560
(Nature is great.)

489
00:44:45,560 --> 00:44:48,160
(Some people think the path
heaven chooses for them)

490
00:44:49,080 --> 00:44:50,880
(is too grand to turn down.)

491
00:44:58,520 --> 00:45:01,760
(Some get bored and abandon their way.)

492
00:45:16,240 --> 00:45:19,440
(Some stick to their path, unmoving.)

493
00:45:26,040 --> 00:45:27,880
(Whatever their path is,)

494
00:45:28,520 --> 00:45:31,360
(vast or narrow,)

495
00:45:32,760 --> 00:45:35,120
APPLICATION FOR
UNDERGRADUATE PROGRAM
(only we know where to go.)

496
00:45:35,120 --> 00:45:36,040
(only we know where to go.)

497
00:45:36,640 --> 00:45:37,800
That’s ’cause all you do is copy!

498
00:45:37,880 --> 00:45:40,200
You should put your
father’s name down, not his!

499
00:45:40,480 --> 00:45:40,960
Told you I didn’t know!

500
00:45:40,960 --> 00:45:45,360
(Still there are people whose principles
are stronger than any heaven’s will.)

501
00:45:50,680 --> 00:45:54,920
HEAVEN IS ONLY AS GREAT AS YOUR MIND WRITTEN BY MASTER TONG

502
00:45:56,280 --> 00:45:57,360
(And they can all say)

503
00:45:59,480 --> 00:46:01,520
(that they forge their own paths.)

504
00:46:09,320 --> 00:46:15,200
(Sometimes, your intellect, ego,
and fear misguide you)

505
00:46:18,040 --> 00:46:19,480
(and make you lose your way.)

506
00:46:22,800 --> 00:46:25,760
(But once you allow yourself
to be a part of nature,)

507
00:46:27,440 --> 00:46:30,440
(heaven becomes a part of us.)

508
00:46:32,800 --> 00:46:35,520
(That is when you will find your way.)

509
00:47:38,320 --> 00:47:39,840
How did you know I’d be here?

510
00:47:43,840 --> 00:47:46,480
Did you forget our souls are intertwined?

511
00:47:47,920 --> 00:47:49,280
I can feel you

512
00:47:50,400 --> 00:47:52,040
just as much as you can feel me.

513
00:47:59,320 --> 00:48:00,680
Does that mean…

514
00:48:02,160 --> 00:48:03,480
Wherever I am,

515
00:48:05,920 --> 00:48:07,280
you’ll find me?

516
00:48:09,400 --> 00:48:09,800
Yes.

517
00:48:11,040 --> 00:48:12,400
You can’t run away from me.

518
00:48:13,360 --> 00:48:16,360
You still owe me for the house.

519
00:48:17,080 --> 00:48:18,840
Wow, you jerk.

520
00:48:20,240 --> 00:48:22,600
I brought you back from
the Life Spirit Realm.

521
00:48:23,480 --> 00:48:25,320
You don’t think that vouches
for some discount?

522
00:48:25,680 --> 00:48:27,360
You’re taking advantage of me, man.

523
00:48:28,760 --> 00:48:29,760
Hmm…

524
00:48:31,200 --> 00:48:32,160
You have a point there.

525
00:48:33,640 --> 00:48:34,040
Alright.

526
00:48:34,280 --> 00:48:36,800
I’ll give you a five-million discount,

527
00:48:37,720 --> 00:48:39,360
which still leaves four million…

528
00:48:41,280 --> 00:48:45,160
I think you might need to work
for me to pay off your debt.

529
00:49:51,200 --> 00:49:55,240
This jade has been passed down
for many generations.

530
00:49:56,120 --> 00:49:57,680
I got it as a gift.

531
00:49:58,400 --> 00:50:00,680
I’m giving it to you now.

532
00:50:01,600 --> 00:50:03,040
Take good care of it.

533
00:50:03,560 --> 00:50:06,640
Will it make me Wu if I wear it?

534
00:50:07,560 --> 00:50:08,000
No.

535
00:50:08,840 --> 00:50:11,040
This piece of jade does not
make anyone Wu,

536
00:50:11,600 --> 00:50:14,000
or make someone what they want to be.

537
00:50:15,120 --> 00:50:19,200
So it has no power whatsoever?

538
00:50:21,120 --> 00:50:21,800
Of course it does.

539
00:50:22,560 --> 00:50:25,040
You will find out one day.

540
00:50:25,600 --> 00:50:29,200
You will understand what power it holds

541
00:50:30,240 --> 00:50:32,080
and how to make use of it.

542
00:51:02,960 --> 00:51:06,560
The evil forces that you’ve encountered, felt, and unknowingly absorbed,

543
00:51:07,120 --> 00:51:08,280
transfer them to me.

544
00:51:14,600 --> 00:51:17,080
So you’re saying I’ve made
your heart feel again?

545
00:51:21,080 --> 00:51:21,760
Pete!

546
00:51:22,800 --> 00:51:24,640
I don’t know what you were like in the past.

547
00:51:25,040 --> 00:51:26,440
But I want you to know…

548
00:51:26,800 --> 00:51:29,040
You have people who accept you,

549
00:51:29,360 --> 00:51:31,360
and are willing to stick by you.

550
00:51:31,880 --> 00:51:34,200
You just need to let them.

551
00:51:52,560 --> 00:51:53,200
Hey!

552
00:51:53,760 --> 00:51:55,000
Focus on the road!

553
00:51:57,360 --> 00:51:59,560
- It’s teamwork!
- No, you jerk!

554
00:51:59,640 --> 00:52:00,600
Don’t be stubborn!

555
00:52:11,080 --> 00:52:13,320
You’re very important to me.

556
00:52:15,440 --> 00:52:19,840
Thank you for doing everything
in your power to bring me back.

557
00:52:22,400 --> 00:52:24,600
When someone I love is in danger,

558
00:52:25,280 --> 00:52:26,480
I need to save them.

559
00:52:33,520 --> 00:52:34,240
Turn off!

560
00:52:36,120 --> 00:52:37,280
You’re a damn dork.

561
00:52:39,360 --> 00:52:42,480
Maybe the reason I agreed to come back

562
00:52:43,080 --> 00:52:45,800
was because I have you
who truly believes in me.

563
00:52:46,760 --> 00:52:49,400
What’s not to believe in?

564
00:52:55,040 --> 00:52:56,040
It belonged to my Mom.

565
00:52:56,400 --> 00:52:58,040
You gave me something of your grandpa’s.

566
00:52:58,280 --> 00:53:00,040
I want to give you something of
my Mom’s in return.

567
00:53:01,520 --> 00:53:02,760
And if it has power,

568
00:53:03,200 --> 00:53:05,320
I want that power to protect you.
